*   [Draw (terrain)](/Draw_(terrain)): A long area of downward-sloping low ground.
*   [Drumlin](/Drumlin): An elongated hill formed by glacial action.
*   [Dry lake](/Dry_lake): An area that once contained a standing surface water body.
*   [Dune](/Dune): A hill of loose sand built by aeolian processes or the flow of water.
