*   [Esker](/Esker): A long, winding ridge of stratified sand and gravel, deposited by meltwater streams.
*   [Estuary](/Estuary): A partially enclosed coastal body of brackish water where freshwater rivers meet the sea.
*   [Exhumed river channel](/Exhumed_river_channel): A ridge of sandstone that remains after softer surrounding rock has eroded away, revealing an ancient riverbed.
