*   [Lavaka](/Lavaka): A specific type of gully formed by groundwater sapping.
*   [Levee](/Levee): A ridge or wall built to hold back water, either natural or artificial.
*   [Limestone pavement](/Limestone_pavement): A natural karst landform consisting of a flat, exposed surface of limestone, dissected by fissures.
*   [Loess](/Loess): Sediment of accumulated wind-blown dust.
*   [Lacustrine terraces](/Terrace_(geology)): Step-like landforms marking former shorelines of a lake.
*   [Maar](/Maar): A low-relief volcanic crater, often formed by phreatomagmatic eruptions.
*   [Machair](/Machair): A fertile, low-lying grassy plain, typically found in Scotland and Ireland.
*   [Malpaís (landform)](/Malpa%C3%ADs_(landform)): A rough and barren landscape of relict and largely uneroded lava fields.
*   [Mamelon (volcanology)](/Mamelon_(volcanology)): A rock formation created by the eruption of relatively thick or stiff lava through a narrow vent.
*   [Marine terrace](/Raised_beach): An emergent coastal landform, a former sea-bed lifted above sea level.
*   [Marsh](/Marsh): A low-lying area of land that is waterlogged or seasonally flooded.
*   [Massif](/Massif): The principal mass of a mountain or mountain range.
*   [Meander](/Meander): One of a series of curves in the channel of a mature stream.
