*   [Raised beach](/Raised_beach): An emergent coastal landform, a former sea-bed lifted above sea level.
*   [Rapids](/Rapids): A section of a river or stream where the water flows with increased velocity and turbulence.
*   [Ravine](/Ravine): A small valley, often deeply incised by stream erosion.
*   [Ria](/Ria): A coastal inlet formed by the partial submergence of a river valley.
*   [Ridge](/Ridge): A long, narrow, elevated landform.
